eat SF area photographer.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:60:\"http://cdn.pagelines.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/logo.png\";s:6:\"length\";s:5:\"14623\";s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"image/jpg\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Henry Perkins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29390:\"<p>I cannot believe it has been a week since <a href=\"http://2012.sf.wordcamp.org\" title=\"WordCamp SF Site\" target=\"_blank\">WordCamp San Francisco</a>!  Check out some of the photos taken at the event by <a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/photo\" title=\"@photo\" target=\"_blank\">Michael O&#8217;Donnell</a> &#8211; Great SF area photographer.</p>\n<p>As you can see below,  <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/search/%23wcsf\" title=\"wcsf hashtag\" target=\"_blank\">#WCSF</a> was a huge success!  I think the most interesting part about the &#8220;State of the Word&#8221; is the term &#8220;App Engine&#8221; that Matt used during his presentation.  The way <a href=\"http://www.wordpress.org/\" title=\"WordPress.org\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress</a> has evolved from a blog, to a CMS, and now into the future as a platform for developing almost anything is exciting!!</p>\n\n<a href=\'http://www.pagelines.com/wordcamp-san-francisco/2012-08-04-11-06-24-2-2/\' title=\'2012-08-04-11-06-24-2\'><img data-attachment-id=\"8784\" data-orig-file=\"http://cdn.pagelines.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/2012-08-04-11-06-24-21.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"2048,1365\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;a